title: Corporate World's Campaign Donations to Democrats and Republicans, 9.2.2007
name: Corporate World's Campaign Donations to Democrats and Republicans, 9.2.2007
description: The map is based on FEC (Federal Election Committee) data on campaign contributions as of Sept 02, 2007. The data was derived from the donations given by Corporate PACs to U.S. Senators and Congressmen from 2006 till today. The Corporate PAC contributed $38.65 million. Out of that Democrats received nearly $19.7 million and Republicans received $18.9 million, a very small (negligible) amount went to Independents and the rest.
